Independent analyst Chris Gilmour chose cash as his stock pick of the day and Drikus Combrinck from Capicraft chose Bidcorp. Gilmour said: “As of a couple of weeks ago I’m still sticking with cash, all I see now are rallies and bear markets.” Combrinck said: “A multinational company called Bidcorp, it’s trading in dollar terms and is 50% down in dollar terms, for good reason as it supplies restaurants and so on. If you are willing to stick it out, they do have a strong balance sheet.” Or listen to the full audio: Subscribe: iono.fm | Apple Podcasts | Pocket Casts | Player.fm